Transmissible spongiform encephalopathies (TSEs) or prion diseases are neurodegenerative diseases that occur in a variety of species, including sheep (scrapie), cattle (bovine spongiform encephalopathy, BSE) and humans (e.g. Creutzfeld to Jakob disease, CJD). A characteristic feature of these diseases is the accumulation of PrPSc, a post-translationally modified form of the host glycoprotein PrPC, in the central nervous system
